# Ryan's Yard — Cursor Rules

## Project
Mobile-first browser sports game built as a birthday gift for Ryan, turning 14.
React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS. Landscape orientation only.
No backend, no auth, no database — pure frontend, deployed to Vercel.

## Identity
- Game name: Ryan's Yard
- Jersey number: #14 (decorative element throughout)
- Color scheme: Jets green (#203731), white, black
- Font: Press Start 2P (Google Fonts, loaded in index.html)
- Aesthetic: 8-bit/16-bit pixel art, neighborhood sports theme

## File Structure
src/
  App.tsx              ← game state machine and screen router (owns all state)
  types.ts             ← shared TypeScript types
  index.css            ← Tailwind directives, CSS variables, font import
  components/
    TitleScreen.tsx
    ScoreScreen.tsx
    RoundIntro.tsx
    RotatePrompt.tsx
  games/
    Baseball.tsx
    Basketball.tsx
    Football.tsx
    Lacrosse.tsx

## State Rules
- App.tsx owns ALL game state via useState (screen, roundIndex, scores)
- Game loop state (positions, timers, RAF handles) lives in useRef — never useState
- Always cancel requestAnimationFrame in the useEffect cleanup function
- Each game component receives: onComplete: (score: number) => void
- Call onComplete when the round ends (strikes out, attempts exhausted, etc.)

## Code Rules
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore` without a written explanation.
- No external asset files — all visuals via CSS, emoji, or inline canvas drawing
- No animation libraries — CSS transitions and requestAnimationFrame only
- Touch targets minimum 48x48px on all interactive elements
- No hover-dependent interactions — touch/tap only
- ESLint + Prettier compliant
- No placeholders, no TODOs, no "add your logic here" stubs in delivered code
- Use CSS variables defined in index.css for all colors (never hardcode hex values)

## Screen Flow
title → round-intro → baseball → round-intro → basketball
      → round-intro → football → round-intro → lacrosse → score → title

## Game Summaries
- Baseball: Pitch flies top→bottom, tap SWING in timing window. 3 strikes ends round.
- Basketball: Vertical shot meter loops. Tap SHOOT in green zone. 10 attempts.
- Football: Receiver runs route, tap THROW to pass to their position. 8 throws.
- Lacrosse: Shot incoming, tap correct save zone (Left/Center/Right). 10 shots.

## Orientation
- Landscape only. CSS media query hides .game-root in portrait, shows .rotate-prompt.
- RotatePrompt.tsx shows fullscreen "ROTATE YOUR PHONE" message in portrait mode.

## Do Not
- Do not add a router (no react-router, no next/router)
- Do not add sound (future enhancement)
- Do not add a leaderboard or any server-side logic
- Do not add hover states
- Do not use any third-party animation library
- Do not use portrait-only layout assumptions anywhere in game components
- Do not add SEO meta tags (this is a game, not a webpage)
- Do not import any external image or audio files
